I"3<p>Arpita was an undergraduate at Birla Institute of Technology and Science and obtained her Ph.D. in Physics from the University of Notre Dame with James Glazier. She was then a postdoctoral fellow and a Pappalardo Fellow at MIT working with Alexander Oudenaarden. Arpita joined University of Maryland in 2006 with a joint appointment in <a href="http://umdphysics.umd.edu">Physics</a> and <a href="http://www.ipst.umd.edu">Institute for Physical Science and Technology</a>. In her (non-existent) spare time, Arpita is an avid photographer and loves hiking.</p>
